The paper deals with the problem of recovering true labels from possibly erroneous crowdsourced labels, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new algorithm based on Belief Propagation (BP) and compares it with existing state-of-the-art algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which makes cs.SI (Signal Processing) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a lower bound on the fundamental limit, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
